        <Markdown>
            Supported formatters:
            - dateFormat
            - date
            - datetime
            - time
            - capitalize
            - number
            - fixed2
            - percent
            - stringify
            - object
        </Markdown>

        <Markdown>
            -----
            ## dateFormat
            format datetime value as date, uses a date-fns format String!
            for help building format string, see https://date-fns-interactive.netlify.app/

            Usage:
            ```xml
                <Data
                    name="dateToFormat"
                    defaultValue="2023-11-16T17:38:24.662Z"
                />
                <Typography
                    textContent="{{ global_dateToFormat:dateFormat[EEEE, MMMM do dd/LL/yyyy hh:mm:ss b O] }}"
                />
            ```
            Expected Output: 
            ```text
            Thursday, November 16th 16/11/2023 05:38:24 PM GMT-5
            ```
            Live Example:
        </Markdown>
        <Typography
            textContent="{{ global_dateToFormat:dateFormat[EEEE, MMMM do dd/LL/yyyy hh:mm:ss b O] }}"
            sx:p="3"
            sx:borderRadius="5px"
            sx:backgroundColor="#fafafa"
        />

        <Markdown>
